---
import BaseLayout from "../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout title="Portfolio Website Case Study">

<h1>Personal Portfolio Website</h1>

<div class="mt-6 grid grid-cols-2 md:grid-cols-4 gap-4 text-sm">
  <div>
    <p class="text-[color:var(--color-text-muted)]">Project Type</p>
    <p class="font-semibold">Personal Portfolio</p>
  </div>

  <div>
    <p class="text-[color:var(--color-text-muted)]">Role</p>
    <p class="font-semibold">Concept, Design, Development</p>
  </div>

  <div>
    <p class="text-[color:var(--color-text-muted)]">Tools</p>
    <p class="font-semibold">Astro, GitHub, Cloudflare Pages</p>
  </div>

  <div>
    <p class="text-[color:var(--color-text-muted)]">Year</p>
    <p class="font-semibold">2026</p>
  </div>
</div>

<hr class="my-8 border-[color:var(--border)]">

<h2>Overview</h2>
<p>
This portfolio website was built to present projects, experiments and
technical tools in a clear and structured way that goes beyond a
traditional CV.
</p>

<h2>Problem</h2>
<p>
A standard resume often cannot show real work, digital projects or the
thinking process behind marketing ideas and experiments.
</p>

<h2>Solution</h2>
<p>
Developed a personal portfolio using Astro and deployed it through
Cloudflare Pages to create a fast, clean and structured presentation of
projects and case studies.
</p>

<h2>Result</h2>
<p>
The website now acts as a central hub for showcasing marketing concepts,
experiments, internal tools and research projects.
</p>

</BaseLayout>
